eqSysSystemId.name: eqSysSystemId
eqSysSystemId.description: The unique value assigned to each chassis at manufacturing time.

eqSysPhysEntLastChangeTime.name: eqSysPhysEntLastChangeTime
eqSysPhysEntLastChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last physical entity change event occurred (e.g. a module was inserted into the system).

eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileAction.name: eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileAction
eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileAction.description: A read of this object always returns the value other(1). Setting this object to copyCfgFile(2) will initiate a save of the current configuration and a copy of the config file on the local filesystem. The progress of this request can be monitored by polling the eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileStatus object. The name of the saved config file, including absolute filesystem path, is stored in the eqSysCfgSavedFilename attribute.

eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileStatus.name: eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileStatus
eqSysCfgCopyConfigFileStatus.description: This object is used to monitor the progress of a request to save and copy the current config file on the local filesystem. The user may also do a set to reset this object to value copyCfgIdle(1).

eqSysCfgSavedFilename.name: eqSysCfgSavedFilename
eqSysCfgSavedFilename.description: The name assigned to the saved config file.

eqEidReqTable.name: eqEidReqTable
eqEidReqTable.description: This table is used to get equipe id values.

eqEidReqIndex.name: eqEidReqIndex
eqEidReqIndex.description: The unique value to identify this entry.

eqEidReqUser.name: eqEidReqUser
eqEidReqUser.description: A textual string to identify the owner of this entry.

eqEidReqCount.name: eqEidReqCount
eqEidReqCount.description: The count of equipe id's requested.

eqEidReqCountAlloc.name: eqEidReqCountAlloc
eqEidReqCountAlloc.description: The count of equipe id's actually allocated.

eqEidReqAction.name: eqEidReqAction
eqEidReqAction.description: A read of this object always returns the value other(1). Setting this object to alloc(2) will cause the agent to allocate new eid's. The number of eid's to allocate is determined by the value of eqEidReqCount object. The agent will create an entry in the eqEidResultTable containing the allocated eid's. The NMS can retrieve these values by doing a getnext using the eqEidReqIndex for this entry as the key.

eqEidReqActionStatus.description: The result of the action requested.

eqEidReqRowStatus.name: eqEidReqRowStatus

eqEidResData.name: eqEidResData

eqModuleRedEid.description: The unique id assigned to the module.

eqModuleRedPeerId.description: The id of the module that is a peer to this module. The peer can be either a primary or a backup module. A value of zero indicates no peer module.

eqModuleRedAction.name: eqModuleRedAction
eqModuleRedAction.description: A read of this object always returns the value other(1). Setting this to switchRole(2) causes the module to switch role with it's peer module.

eqIntfBertTable.name: eqIntfBertTable
eqIntfBertTable.description: This table is used to initiate a Bit Error Rate Test (BERT) on a sonet port and also for reading statistics on the initiated test.

eqIntfBertEid.name: eqIntfBertEid
eqIntfBertEid.description: The eid assigned to the interface.

eqIntfBertMonitorState.name: eqIntfBertMonitorState
eqIntfBertMonitorState.description: The current BERT monitor state. A value of active(1) indicates that a BERT test is currently running.

eqIntfBertMonitorStatus.name: eqIntfBertMonitorStatus
eqIntfBertMonitorStatus.description: The BERT monitor status value. Note that this object is only valid when a BERT test is running.

eqIntfBertMonitorOutOfSyncTime.name: eqIntfBertMonitorOutOfSyncTime
eqIntfBertMonitorOutOfSyncTime.description: The total amount of time, in seconds, that the monitor has been out of synch since the BERT test was started.

eqIntfBertRequestedBitErrorCount.name: eqIntfBertRequestedBitErrorCount
eqIntfBertRequestedBitErrorCount.description: The number of bit errors the user wants inserted onto the interface. This value is used when the user issues a bit error request by a set to the eqIntfBertAction object.

eqIntfBertInsertedBitErrorCount.name: eqIntfBertInsertedBitErrorCount
eqIntfBertInsertedBitErrorCount.description: The actual number of bit errors inserted onto the interface.

eqIntfBertMeasuredByteErrorCount.name: eqIntfBertMeasuredByteErrorCount
eqIntfBertMeasuredByteErrorCount.description: The number of byte errors measured on the interface.

eqIntfBertTestStartTime.name: eqIntfBertTestStartTime
eqIntfBertTestStartTime.description: The time that the test was started.

eqIntfBertTestDuration.name: eqIntfBertTestDuration
eqIntfBertTestDuration.description: The time, in seconds, that the test has been running.

eqIntfBertAction.name: eqIntfBertAction
eqIntfBertAction.description: A read of this object always returns the value other(1). Setting this object to insertBitError(2) inserts a bit error on the interface.
